## Key Concepts
- Azure Policy deny public network access for storage accounts
- Private Endpoints and private DNS configuration
- Resource tagging as policy gates in CI/CD
- Rollback to last known-good ARM/Bicep template
- Monitoring and alerting via Azure Monitor

## Code Example
```json
{
  "properties": {
    "displayName": "Deny public network access on storage accounts",
    "policyType": "Regular",
    "mode": "All",
    "policyRule": {
      "if": {
        "allOf": [
          {"field": "type", "equals": "Microsoft.Storage/storageAccounts"},
          {"field": "Microsoft.Storage/storageAccounts/networkAcls/defaultAction", "equals": "Allow"}
        ]
      },
      "then": {"effect": "Deny"}
